# 13. Knowledge Ingestion

Books, repositories, and structured notes can be ingested using:

```
python ingest_books.py <path>
```

Supported inputs:

* PDF files
* EPUB files
* Entire repositories (source code, markdown, text)
* Notes collections

Examples:

Ingest a single PDF:

```
python ingest_books.py book.pdf --type book --year 2023
```

Ingest a repository:

```
python ingest_books.py ./my_repo --type repo --year 2024
```

Ingest everything in current directory:

```
python ingest_books.py *
```

Metadata can be provided via:

* CLI arguments (`--source`, `--year`, `--type`)
* metadata.txt file

Each ingested chunk is stored with:

* source
* type
* year
* ingested_at

Chunking strategy:

* Text: semantic paragraph grouping (~300 words per chunk)
* Code: block-based segmentation (~80 lines per chunk)

Newer sources are prioritized during retrieval when similarity scores are comparable.

