# 14. Deployment and Usage Scope

This system is designed for production-style academic knowledge systems.

It supports:

* Local CLI usage
* REST API integration
* Web UI integration
* Mobile app integration
* Structured repository indexing
* Book-based tutoring systems
* Long-term persistent knowledge bases

The architecture allows integration into:

* Internal knowledge platforms
* Educational tools
* Research assistants
* Code-aware tutoring systems

The system serves as a controlled AI middleware layer between clients and language models.

---

# 15. Known Limitations

* No horizontal scaling built-in
* Rule-based safety layer
* No automatic ingestion scheduler
* No built-in authentication layer for API
* No web browsing capability
* Indexes stored locally
* Backend model availability depends on configured provider

These limitations are architectural decisions to maintain determinism, modularity, and system transparency.

---

# 16. Architectural Integrity

Strict responsibility separation is enforced:

* Router does not retrieve
* Retriever does not rank
* Memory system performs ranking and metadata handling
* Prompt builder does not route
* Engine orchestrates only
* LLM interface abstracts provider implementation
* Ingestion pipeline is independent of runtime inference

Academic answering is retrieval-first and chunk-grounded.

The system prioritizes:

* Deterministic behavior
* Metadata-aware ranking
* Controlled context construction
* Low hallucination generation
* Persistent knowledge storage
* Backend-agnostic model communication

